rest_of_day_open: The weekend I am off, so I will spend it with friends doing fall things, relaxing, talking about life, and watching movies, eating good food. Later in the week I will do homework for my class, work on my house things, and go to work.  I have a lot to get done this next week.
critical_positive: We were able to keep the conversation going pretty much the entire time, even though  we do not have many common interests. He talked about being an introvert and likely video games. I talked about my random hobbies, working at the hospital, then about video games to kill the time.
critical_negative: We did not have much in common which made it hard to keep the conversation up, although we did a great job of that anyways. The video was fine, the quality a little blurry but no issues with sound or video gaps.  There were no major concerns. It worked well.

begin_memory_text: We talked about what was expected of us for this video chat thing. We talked about where we're from, what our jobs are. We talked about how COVID has been and how we've been dealing with it.
middle_memory_text: We talked about our hobbies, and our jobs. I talked about how COVID affected me and changed my career path. We discussed other things that I don't really remember. Maybe tastes in music? There was some video game chat.
end_memory_text: I mentioned how we are complete opposites and found that interesting after I had assumed everyone on Prolific was more of a introverted homebody type of person. We talked more about video games, specifically older Sega Genesis games. Honestly, through the whole conversation, you could probably cut the awkwardness with a knife. And I don't fault either of us for it. LOL
rest_of_day_open: The rest of my week is just the weekend. I don't have to work and will get some much appreciated rest and relaxation. My girlfriend and I will be going out to a friend's house to watch some horror movies tomorrow night. Past that, I have no real plans. I will probably play video games and watch youtube videos.
critical_positive: What worked well is that I tried my best to keep the conversation going. If I didn't, I'm not really convinced any conversation would have happened. She was at least kind and open to talking about whatever topics I would bring up. We were able to relate a little on playing older video games as kids.
critical_negative: She didn't really seem interested in talking about anything. She barely tried to bring up topics and seemed bored throughout the conversation, which I totally get. After working all day, it is difficult to summon up the energy to have conversation. I've had to force myself to converse for this research because I have only been doing after working a whole shift of talking to random people. We had nothing in common at all really, and had nothing to relate to.
